cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the 5G NR standard for wireless communications and proposes a solution to mitigate blockages in mmWave networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper analyses the expected data rate of a mmWave system under different blockage scenarios. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of mmWave spectrum to improve access network capacity. 
- cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) is another possible category as mmWave networks are expected to play a crucial role in enabling AR/VR applications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper proposes a solution to adapt the slot-time in order to mitigate the blockage effects, which can be seen as a control problem.
